codex
The proven path is the P0 kernel: it creates real Git worktrees, commits three distinct implementations, runs subprocess tests, selects a measured leader, records the initial adversarial failure, commits a repair, retests, and emits a receipt/genome/Build Truth. I’m wrapping that implementation with a cross-platform judge verifier that independently gates every claim and performs tamper tests on disposable copies, leaving the pristine generated proof verifiable.
